<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Aldi has recalled on Jack 'N' Jill Wooden Block Sets (Farm, Jungle and Ocean</p>

<p>Aldi has urgently recalled a popular children's toy over fears kids could choke to death. </p>

<p>The supermarket giant has issued a recall on Jack 'N' Jill Wooden Block Sets (Farm, Jungle and Ocean).</p>

<p>The affected products were sold at ALDI stores in NSW, VIC, QLD, SA, ACT, and WA from June 10 to September 9. </p>

<p>Small magnets may detach from the blocks and fall off, which poses a risk of choking, suffocation or death for young children.</p>

<p>Consumers should immediately stop using the products and return them to the nearest ALDI store for a full refund. </p>

<p>'ALDI takes product quality and safety seriously,' the chain said is a statement on Facebook. </p>

<p>'We apologise for any inconvenience.' </p>

<p>The affected products (pictured) were sold at Aldi stores across the country from June 10 to September 9</p>

<p>Aldi announced the recall in a statement online, saying it 'takes product quality and safety seriously'</p>
